						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of “half” a perpetual lamp to the temple of Śrīyāṟṟuttaḷi-Mahādēva at Parāntaka-chaturvēdimaṅgalam in Muḍiyūr-nāḍu of Tirumuṉaippāḍi-nāḍu, a division of Rājendraśōḻa-vaḷanāḍu by Peṟṟān (Periyāṉ ?) Uttaman, a farmer of the village for the merit of Peṟṟāṉ Sōmaṉ (probably his brother).</p>						

						</summary>
